To create components in ClojureScript using Reagent, you would typically define a function that returns hiccup-like syntax, a vector of values that Reagent will translate into React components. The `use-state` hook equivalent in Reagent is achieved using `reagent.core/atom`. For managing lifecycle methods similar to `componentDidMount`, you can use `reagent.core/create-class` with `:component-did-mount` method or `reagent.core/use-effect`.

